The paper deals with the storage and delivery of data in cloud infrastructure, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The use of replication and erasure coding techniques for data dissemination and delivery involves network protocols and communication systems (cs.NI). The development of mathematical models and analysis of delivery policies falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper also discusses performance bounds, which could be related to Performance Analysis and Optimization (cs.PF).
